[1] Viet Nam
Date: Sun 13 Nov 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Thanh Nien News, 11 Nov 2005 [edited]
<http://www.thanhniennews.com/print.php?catid=8&newsid=10490>

Viet Nam grapples with bird flu epidemic
---------------------------------------------
Viet Nam's animal health agency said Friday [11 Nov 2005] that bird
flu had spread to 30 communes in 9 provinces and cities, where nearly
30 000 fowl died or were culled.
The provinces are Bac Lieu and Dong Thap in the south, Thanh Hoa in
the center, Bac Giang, Quang Nam, Hai Duong, Hung Yen, and Ninh Binh
in the north, in addition to the capital, Hanoi.
200 fighting cocks belonging to a family in Quang Nam died Thursday
[10 Nov 2005] of suspected bird flu. The province's Department of
Animal Health culled 1500 chickens later the same day.
