<http://en.chinabroadcast.cn/2238/2005-11-13/88@281799.htm>

Bird Flu Controls Stepped Up Across China
-----------------------------------------------
Most Chinese cities and provinces have taken further strong steps to
prevent and control avian influenza, according to the Chinese
Ministry of Agriculture.
It is reported that local communities have set up contingency plans
against a serious animal epidemic, and increased funds and resources
are being devoted to the prevention and control of bird flu.
Governments have also proposed that the density of poultry farming
should be reduced and that the monitoring of flocks for bird flu be
intensified to prevent the disease from spreading.
Cases of infection with the deadly H5N1 avian flu virus, which is
highly infectious in birds, have occurred in China's Inner Mongolia
region and in Anhui, Hunan, Liaoning and Hubei provinces since the
middle of October 2005.
Government departments have culled over 10 million domestic birds in
the infected areas.
